<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-839-952  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 839 952.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Sept 3 1990 v4 n32 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CIM to name interim DOD IRM systems. (Defense Department'sCorporate Information Management; Department of Defense;information resources management)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Defense Department's (DOD) Corporate Information Management(CIM) will select software that will serve as interim standardinformation systems for the DOD, until 12 CIM groups review thedepartment's information systems requirements.andP;  The groups willstudy such areas as warehousing, materials management, personnel,payroll, financial operations, medical and government-furnishedproperty and contract payment.andP;  The functional requirements willultimately be used to develop standard information systems for thedepartment.andP;  The interim systems could be chosen as DOD-widestandard information systems, depending on whether they do therequired job and whether they save the department money.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information SystemsSoftware SelectionStandardsApplicationsGovernment AgencyUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>